About HTML, CSS & JavaScript
  HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are the three core technologies of front-end web development. Together, they are used to build modern, responsive, and interactive websites and web applications.
    -HTML (HyperText Markup Language) creates the structure and content of a webpage.
    -CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) styles the webpage by adding colors, fonts, layouts, spacing, and responsive designs.
    -JavaScript adds interactivity and dynamic functionality, such as handling user actions, updating content, and integrating APIs.

Where are they commonly used?
  HTML, CSS, and JavaScript are widely used in:
    - Business and company websites
    - E-commerce websites
    - Portfolio websites
    - Blogs and news portals
    - Social media platforms
    - Online learning platforms
    - Banking and finance applications
    - Healthcare applications
    - Travel and booking websites
    - Admin dashboards
    - Web-based management systems
    - Single Page Applications (SPAs)

Advantages:
  - Easy to learn and widely supported
  - Compatible with all modern web browsers
  - Creates responsive and user-friendly websites
  - Improves website performance and user experience
  - Enables dynamic and interactive web pages
  - Supports API integration and real-time data
  - Forms the foundation of modern front-end development
  - Works seamlessly with frameworks like React, Angular, and Vue
